Package com.cognex.dataman.sdk.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CameraPermissionException
    Represents an error if there is no permission to access phone camera
    DataManException
    Base class for all DataMan SDK exceptions.
    DataManOperationException
    Base class for all operation-related DataMan SDK exceptions.
    IncorrectChecksumException
    Represents the error that caused by a rejected command because of a checksum mismatch.
    InvalidCommandException
    Represents the error that caused by a rejected command.
    InvalidParameterException
    Represents the error that caused by a rejected command because of an invalid parameter.
    LoginFailedException
    Thrown when authentication to a remote system fails during the connection process.
    MXConnectException
    MXConnect related exception
    NoAccessoryDeviceException  
    OperationCanceledException
    Represents the error that caused by a command which was canceled.
    ParameterRejectedException
    Represents the error that caused by a rejected command because of a rejected parameter.
    SystemOfflineException
    Represents the error that caused by the offline reader that can't accept commands.
    UnknownErrorException
    Represents the unidentified error that returned from the remote system.
    UnsupportedCameraModeException
    Represents an error if camera mode is not supported
